OL,4,CQuebec top court upholds most of
OL,5,Creligious symbols secularism bill
OL,6, A Canadian court has largely upheld a
OL,7, controversial Quebec law barring civil
OL,8, servants in positions of "authority"
OL,9, from wearing religious symbols at work.
OL,11,FBut the province's top court struck
OL,12,Fdown parts of the law that applied to
OL,13,FEnglish-speaking public schools.
OL,15,FBill 21 prevents judges, police
OL,16,Fofficers, teachers and public servants
OL,17,Ffrom wearing symbols such as the
OL,18,Fkippah, turban, or hijab while at work.
OL,20,FAdopted in June 2019, it has fuelled
OL,21,Ffierce debate throughout the country.
